President Obama has announced his intention to nominate Dr. William "Bro" Adams as Chairman of the National Endowment for the Humanities. Dr. Adams is currently the President of Colby College and has previously held leadership positions at Bucknell University and Wesleyan University. He has also served as a program coordinator at Stanford University and has held teaching positions at various universities. Dr. Adams is a Vietnam War veteran and has conducted research in France as a Fulbright Scholar. He is a member of the Board of Directors of the Maine Film Center and the Maine Public Broadcasting Corporation. Dr. Adams holds a B.A. from the Colorado College and a Ph.D. from the University of California, Santa Cruz. President Obama praised Dr. Adams' leadership and experience in the field of humanities and expressed his confidence in his ability to lead the nation's cultural agency.